name: Manaaki - NZ Birds
description:
Manaaki - 1. (verb) (-tia) to support, take care of, 
give hospitality to, protect, look out for.

We love Aotearoa and feel pretty lucky to live in  such a beautiful place. So naturally, we feel passionate about seeing it remain thriving with beautiful birds and lush fauna.

As a way of showing how much we care, we have created our Manaaki bird bookmark series and will donate $1 from every bookmark sold directly to the Royal Forest and Bird Protection Society of New Zealand.

Please use the drop down menu to select the image you would like. 

Each bookmark comes packaged with beautiful textured card stock and in a simple cello sleeve as seen in the last photo.

The bookmarks are made from laminating 2 different wood veneers together and then are finished with a waterbased varathane, to make sure your bookmark and it's image are long lasting. In keeping with our desire to recycle as much as possible, our veneer is usually off cuts, scraps or taken from furniture we have found. If you would like a specific wood to be used in your bookmark, please convo us to see if it is available. Some common veneers we use are Maple, Birdseye Maple, Oak, Cherry, Mahogony & Walnut. 

Measures approx 6" x 1.5"
